docs.abstract: At hearings of the Senate Finance Committee and House Committee on Oversight and Reform, Republicans and Democrats warned that the days of unchecked drug price increases might be ending.
docs.snippet: At hearings of the Senate Finance Committee and House Committee on Oversight and Reform, Republicans and Democrats warned that the days of unchecked drug price increases might be ending.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Members of Congress from both parties served notice on pharmaceutical companies on Tuesday that the days of unchecked drug-price increases were over and that they would be held politically accountable for exorbitant prices.

headline.main: On Both Ends of Capitol, Both Parties Warn Big Pharma on Drug Prices

docs.abstract: Prosecutors in Manhattan demanded documents about the committee’s donors, including whether it received illegal foreign donations.
docs.snippet: Prosecutors in Manhattan demanded documents about the committee’s donors, including whether it received illegal foreign donations.
docs.lead_paragraph: Escalating one of the investigations into President Trump’s inaugural committee, federal prosecutors ordered on Monday that its officials turn over documents about donors, finances and activities, according to two people familiar with the inquiry.

headline.main: Trump Inaugural Committee Ordered to Hand Over Documents to Federal Investigators
headline.print_headline: Federal Inquiry Wants Records For Inaugural

byline.original: By Maggie Haberman and Ben Protess

docs.abstract: The House Intelligence Committee began a broad inquiry into whether Russia and other foreign powers may be exercising influence over President Trump.
docs.snippet: The House Intelligence Committee began a broad inquiry into whether Russia and other foreign powers may be exercising influence over President Trump.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The House Intelligence Committee on Wednesday began a broad inquiry into whether Russia and other foreign powers may be exercising influence over President Trump, acting only hours after a defiant Speaker Nancy Pelosi declared that the House would not be cowed by the president’s “all-out threat” to drop its investigations of his administration.

headline.main: Asked to Stop Investigations, House Digs In
headline.print_headline: Asked to Stop Investigations, House Digs In

docs.abstract: Seeking to appeal to a broader swath of the public and end the government shutdown, President Trump alienated portions of his hard-right base and made no headway with Democratic congressional leaders.
docs.snippet: Seeking to appeal to a broader swath of the public and end the government shutdown, President Trump alienated portions of his hard-right base and made no headway with Democratic congressional leaders.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Immigrant advocates denounced it as cruel. The conservative right howled that it was amnesty.

headline.main: In Trump’s Immigration Announcement, a Compromise Snubbed All Around
headline.print_headline: Trump Goes Beyond His Base and No One Is Happy

docs.abstract: President Trump slammed a table, then stormed out of a negotiating session with Democrats, declaring it “a total waste of time” as the shutdown stretches on.
docs.snippet: President Trump slammed a table, then stormed out of a negotiating session with Democrats, declaring it “a total waste of time” as the shutdown stretches on.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump stormed out of a White House meeting with congressional leaders on Wednesday after Speaker Nancy Pelosi said she would not fund a border wall even if he agreed to reopen the government, escalating a confrontation that has shuttered large portions of the government for 19 days and counting.

headline.main: Trump Storms Out of White House Meeting With Democrats on Shutdown
headline.print_headline: Trump Walks Out When Pelosi Says No to Wall Funds

byline.original: By Nicholas Fandos, Michael Tackett and Julie Hirschfeld Davis

docs.abstract: In an interview in rural Kentucky, former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. tested themes for a possible 2020 campaign to unseat President Trump.
docs.snippet: In an interview in rural Kentucky, former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. tested themes for a possible 2020 campaign to unseat President Trump.
docs.lead_paragraph: OWINGSVILLE, Ky. — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr., in some of his harshest criticism of President Trump to date, said on Friday that the president was “trashing American values” and undermining institutions to “amass power,” as he appealed to his party to not give up on winning the votes of the white working class.

headline.main: Joe Biden Doesn’t Hold Back on Trump: He’s ‘Trashing American Values’
headline.print_headline: Biden Doesn’t Hold Back on President: He’s ‘Trashing American Values’

docs.abstract: Democrats avoided any outbursts or walkouts that could have presented a bad image, but their silence as Republicans clapped repeatedly spoke volumes.
docs.snippet: Democrats avoided any outbursts or walkouts that could have presented a bad image, but their silence as Republicans clapped repeatedly spoke volumes.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The State of the Union address is usually the president’s moment to make his case with soaring words. But newly empowered Democrats on Tuesday delivered their own pointed message to President Trump and the nation: We’re back and we won’t be pushed around.

headline.main: State of the Union Speech Puts Democratic Resurgence on Full Display
headline.print_headline: Address Let Democrats Put Defiance on Display

docs.abstract: Senator Richard M. Burr, the chairman of the Intelligence Committee, did not endorse a ban on Chinese equipment, but said American companies must understand the risks.
docs.snippet: Senator Richard M. Burr, the chairman of the Intelligence Committee, did not endorse a ban on Chinese equipment, but said American companies must understand the risks.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Richard M. Burr, the head of the Senate Intelligence Committee, warned American corporations on Wednesday that using Chinese technology in next-generation telecommunication networks could pose security risks, but stopped short of endorsing a ban on such equipment that the Trump administration is considering.

headline.main: Key Senator Warns of Dangers of Chinese Investment in 5G Networks

docs.abstract: “In this time of division and crisis, we must come together and stand for and with one another,” Stacey Abrams said.

docs.lead_paragraph: Stacey Abrams, a former candidate for governor in Georgia, delivered the Democratic response on Tuesday to President Trump’s State of the Union address.

headline.main: Full Transcript: Stacey Abrams Democratic Rebuttal

docs.abstract: In his State of the Union address, the president toggled between conciliation and confrontation, and demanded a wall on the nation’s southwestern border.
docs.snippet: In his State of the Union address, the president toggled between conciliation and confrontation, and demanded a wall on the nation’s southwestern border.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump delivered a message of bipartisan unity on Tuesday night in his first address to Congress in the new era of divided government, but signaled that he would continue to wage war for the hard-line immigration policies that have polarized the capital and the nation.

headline.main: Trump Asks for Unity, but Presses Hard Line on Immigration
headline.print_headline: Asking For Unity, Trump Renews Bid For Border Wall
